 Figure 5.21: A full binary tree. 
**complete binary tree.** A complete binary tree is one in which every level has all possible nodes present, except perhaps for the deepest level, which is filled all the way from the left. Figure 5.21 is not complete, but it would be if we fixed it up as in Figure 5.22. 
