##### II 
 Reports, articles, and books from credible nonacademic sources Well-researched and even-handed descriptions of an event or state of the world Initial research on events or trends not yet analyzed in the academic literature; may reference important Tier 1 sources Websites of relevant agencies, Google searches using *.gov or *.org sites, academic article databases 
##### Tier 
##### III 
 Short pieces from newspapers or credible websites Simple reporting of events, research findings, or policy changes Often point to useful Tier 2 or Tier 1 sources; may provide a factoid or two not found anywhere else Strategic Google searches or article databases, including newspapers and magazines 
##### Tier 
