 No, but close. It satisfies antisymmetry and transitivity, which are crucial. The only thing it doesn't satisfy is reflexivity, since none of the members appear with themselves. If we changed this relation to ranksAtLeastAsHighAs, then we could include these "double" pairs and have ourselves a partial order. 
