into a fresh tree in a beneficial order. What order should we insert them in? Well, remember that whichever node is inserted first will be the root. This suggests that we'd want to insert the _middle_ node first into our tree, so that Molly becomes the new root. This leaves half the nodes for her left subtree and half for her right. If you follow this process logically (and recursively) you'll realize that we'd next want to insert the middle nodes _of each half._ This would equate to Jennifer and Randi (in either order). I think of it like the markings on a ruler: first you insert half an inch, then 1 4 and^ 
 3 4 inches, then^ 
 1 8 ,^ 
