**1.** Google provides some great tips for getting the most out of Google     Scholar. 
**2.** This resource from Bowling Green State University explains how searching     subject headings in a database (compared to keywords) can more quickly     bring you to relevant sources. 
**3.** Explore your university's library website! They may have tutorials,     workshops, major-specific librarians, course guides, and more to help you     in your research process. 
