51. So really what you have here is 50 different sums of 101 each, so the answer is 50 x 101 = 5050. In general, if you add the numbers from 1 to x, where x is any integer at all, you'll get x 2 sums of x + 1 
each, so the answer will be x(x 2 +1). 
Now, use mathematical induction to prove that Gauss was right 
